ctions which cannot be memoized without leading to stale UI. To prevent this, by default React Compiler will skip memoizing this component/hook. However, you may see issues if values from this API are passed to other components/hooks that are memoized.\n\nD:\\my_dev\\SION-Media\\src\\renderer\\src\\components\\library\\LibraryNumberView.tsx:50:26\n  48 |\n  49 |   // eslint-disable-next-line react-hooks/incompatible-library\n> 50 |   const rowVirtualizer = useVirtualizer<HTMLDivElement, HTMLDivElement>({\n     |                          ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^ TanStack Virtual's `useVirtualizer()` API returns functions that cannot be memoized safely\n  51 |     count: rowCount,\n  52 |     getScrollElement: () => parentRef.current,\n  53 |     estimateSize: () => cellSize + gapSize,",["434"],"Compilation Skipped: Use of incompatible library\n\nThis API returns functions which cannot be memoized without leading to stale UI. To prevent this, by default React Compiler will skip memoizing this component/hook. However, you may see issues if values from this API are passed to other components/hooks that are memoized.\n\nD:\\my_dev\\SION-Media\\src\\renderer\\src\\components\\library\\LibraryTitleView.tsx:58:26\n  56 |\n  57 |   // eslint-disable-next-line react-hooks/incompatible-library\n> 58 |   const rowVirtualizer = useVirtualizer<HTMLDivElement, HTMLDivElement>({\n     |                          ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^ TanStack Virtual's `useVirtualizer()` API returns functions that cannot be memoized safely\n  59 |     count: sortedSongs.length,\n  60 |     getScrollElement: () => parentRef.current,\n  61 |     estimateSize: () => 72,",["435"],"Compilation Skipped: Use of incompatible library\n\nThis API returns functions which cannot be memoized without leading to stale UI. To prevent this, by default React Compiler will skip memoizing this component/hook. However, you may see issues if values from this API are passed to other components/hooks that are memoized.\n\nD:\\my_dev\\SION-